#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:294
msgid ""
":guilabel:`MC Name field` |input_list|: select the vector field "
"corresponding to MC Name;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:295
msgid ""
":guilabel:`C ID field` |input_list|: select the vector field "
"corresponding to C ID;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:296
msgid ""
":guilabel:`C Name field` |input_list|: select the vector field "
"corresponding to C Name;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:297
msgid ""
"|checkbox| :guilabel:`Calculate sig.`: if checked, the spectral signature"
" is calculated while the ROI is saved to :ref:`training_input`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:298
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Import vector` |enter|: import all the vector polygons as ROIs"
" in the :ref:`training_input`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:303
msgid "Download USGS Spectral Library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:309
msgid ":guilabel:`Download USGS Spectral Library`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:311
msgid ""
"The tab :guilabel:`Download USGS Spectral Library` allows for the "
"download of the `USGS spectral library <http://speclab.cr.usgs.gov"
"/spectral-lib.html>`_ (Clark, R.N., Swayze, G.A., Wise, R., Livo, E., "
"Hoefen, T., Kokaly, R., Sutley, S.J., 2007, USGS digital spectral library"
" splib06a: U.S. Geological Survey, Digital Data Series 231)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:313
msgid ""
"The libraries are grouped in chapters including Minerals, Mixtures, "
"Coatings, Volatiles, Man-Made, Plants, Vegetation Communities, Mixtures "
"with Vegetation, and Microorganisms. An internet connection is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:316
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Select a chapter` |input_list|: select one of the library "
"chapters; after the selection, chapter libraries are shown in "
":guilabel:`Select a library`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:317
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Select a library` |input_list|: select one of the libraries; "
"the library description is displayed in the frame :guilabel:`Library "
"description`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:318
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Import spectral library` |enter|: download the library and add"
" the sampled spectral signature to the :ref:`ROI_list` using the "
"parameters defined for class and macroclass; the library is automatically"
" sampled according to the image band wavelengths defined in the "
":guilabel:`active band set` in :ref:`band_set_tab`, and added to the "
":ref:`ROI_list`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../importSignaturesTab.rst:320
msgid ""
"**TIP**: Spectral libraries downloaded from the ``USGS Spectral Library``"
" can be used with Minimum Distance or Spectral Angle Mapping algorithms, "
"but not Maximum Likelihood because this algorithm needs the covariance "
"matrix that is not included in the spectral libraries."
msgstr ""

